The OSHA safety requirements for tank gauging operations include:
* Implementing alternative tank gauging and sampling procedures to minimize worker exposures to hydrocarbon gases and vapors [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Retrofitting existing tanks with dedicated sampling ports to eliminate the need to routinely open thief hatches [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Providing appropriate respiratory protection, including supplied air respirators (SAR) and self-contained breathing apparatus (SCBA) [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Providing hazard communication training in a language that employees understand [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Ensuring that workers are trained on and correctly use calibrated multi-gas and oxygen monitors [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Not permitting employees to work alone during tank gauging operations [OSHA 3843, Page 6]
* Ensuring that workers understand the limitations of multi-gas and oxygen monitors and take appropriate actions in case of an alarm or health symptoms [OSHA 3843, Page 6]

